data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
The Mouse Jiggler application resides in the system tray and all functionality is contained within the tray icon. Right clicking on the Mouse Jiggler icon will produce a context menu containing the available options.
Enable Jiggle Toggle: Turns the jiggler on or off. NOTE: Double-Clicking the tray icon will toggle the jiggler on or off.
Ghost Jiggle: Toggles the ghost jiggle mode on or off. The ghost jiggle option uses the operating system interupts to virtually jiggle the mouse.
About: Displays version and license info.
Help: You're already here!
Exit: Closes the Mouse Jiggler application. NOTE: Only one Mouse Jiggler can be running at any given time.
